OL,3,ETHE FOUNTAIN OF YOUTH, WHAT AM I TO DO?
OL,5,GWhy mess up so bad in your reply to    
OL,6,GGerry Ross (24/9)? He's right, the N64 
OL,7,Gis technically a 32-bit console. It has
OL,8,Ga 32-bit CPU and 64-bit graphics chip. 
OL,9,GYou always quote a machine's power by  
OL,10,Gthe CPU, not the graphics chips.       
OL,12,GMy P200 has a fitted 64-bit graphics   
OL,13,Gcard, but it is still a 32-bit machine 
OL,14,Gbecause it has a 32-bit processor at   
OL,15,Gits heart. And I know, I repair PCs for
OL,16,Ga living!BKarl Smith, Cumbria          
OL,18,FThat's all well and good, but the point
OL,19,Fis this: we don't care.                
